added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: The Console
added.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

added.title: The Ollie
added.description: When Darwin asks Gumball to teach him how to skate, Gumball makes sure he covers every aspect of the skating lifestyle from wearing the right gear, using the right terms and choosing the right board. But when Darwin finally gets his wheels rolling, he realizes there might be one important aspect of skating Gumball hasn't taught him.

added.title: The Catfish
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin realise Grandpa Louie has no friends on Elmore Plus, they feel bad so they create one called Muriel. However when Granny Jojo finds out Louie has been spending time online with another 'woman', Muriel not existing isn't going to stop her from being destroyed.

added.title: The Cycle
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

added.title: Craig to the Future
added.description: The Witches of the Creek use their mystical powers to give Craig and his friends a glimpse into the future.

added.title: Craig of the Street
added.description: Craig visits his cousin, Bryson, and they go on a quest through the streets of New Jersey.

added.title: Copycat Carter
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon Carter, the cardboard genius turned cyborg, and Craig decides to help Carter become a kid again, just like him!

added.title: Meat House
added.description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

added.title: Pirate Parrot Polly
added.description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

added.title: Baby Bear Genius
added.description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

added.title: Bug City Sleuths
added.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

added.title: Bubble Fields
added.description: The Bears try to prove to Unica that they can be expert bubble-ologists.

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: Good Job
added.description: Falafel is starting to feel very underappreciated as the building's handyman. What's the point in all this back breaking work if not a single person will ever tell him, "Good Job"?

added.title: One Hit Wonder
added.description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

added.title: A Matter of Pride
added.description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

added.title: Eyesore a Sunset
added.description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: It Could've Been Great
added.description: The Gems take a trip to the moon.

added.title: Message Received
added.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

added.title: Too Far
added.description: Amethyst and Steven get in on some Gem gossip.

added.title: The Answer
added.description: Garnet finally tells Steven the story of how she came to be a Crystal Gem.

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: The 11th Alien
added.description: Ben must overcome his doubts and fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat Vilgax and the Weatherheads.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 3
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: The Visitor
added.description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: Pee Pee G's/Boy Toys
added.description: The Pee Pee G's: When the girls wake up to discover their bed is wet, none of them want to admit that they are the guilty party./Boy Toys: The girls allow Princess to become a Powerpuff Girl when they realize they need help trying to defeat the Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Save Mojo/Substitute Creature
added.description: Save Mojo: An animal activist group sets out to protect Mojo, ensuring that he can behave like the naturally evil monkey that he is./Substitute Creature: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks and the girls are sure that this creature teacher is up to no good.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: The Bubbles-Sitters Club
added.description: Bubbles tries to prove that she's responsible enough to own a dog.

added.title: Elements Part 7: Hero Heart
added.description: A full-scale war has broken out between two kingdoms and it's up to Ooo's most unlikely hero to stop it!

added.title: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
added.description: With time running out, Finn and Lumpy Space Princess work together to unlock one of Ooo's greatest secrets.

added.title: Abstract
added.description: As Jake goes through some personal changes, he's haunted by a sinister dream encounter with his brother Jermaine.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Broken Boogie
added.description: When the Boogie Man loses his mojo, Uncle Grandpa steps in to help.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Uncle Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in trouble! If only he could call an Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Lab Cat
added.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Nuclear Family Values
added.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

added.title: Zombie King
added.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

added.title: Galaxy Jest
added.description: Joker is abducted into space by Mongul to entertain Mongul's troops. Unless the Justice League can re-capture him in time, a Joker gas bomb will go off in Gotham threatening the city.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: El regreso de Xingo
added.description: Cuando Ben debe divertirse solo durante la merecida siesta de Max, se topa con un juego de Xingo y decide convertirse en OE-Shock Rock para encenderlo. Pero cuando Xingo recibe demasiada carga, salta al mundo real, y nuestro héroe debe quedar frente a frente con su personaje animado favorito.

added.title: Cazarecompensas
added.description: Mientras Gwen escucha una conferencia sobre el Ferrocarril Transcontinental, Ben se escapa en secreto a la tienda de regalos. Pero una vez que los Cazarrecompensas aparecen y acorralan a nuestro héroe, Gwen debe transmitir la información que aprendió en el tren y utilizarla para ayudar a Ben a escapar.

added.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
added.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

added.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
added.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
added.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

added.title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
added.description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

added.title: Lost and Found
added.description: When Thomas helps Nia make a delivery to the beach in Norramby, he insists he knows a shortcut and leads the way! But it turns out his memory isn't as good as he… remembered.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas' Day Off
added.description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Real Number One
added.description: When Thomas' #1 is covered by paint, he sets out to prove to himself that he is still number one, but when everything starts to go wrong for him, he learns what it really means to be #1.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Dia de los Muertos
added.description: Blippi wonders how do you celebrate Dia De Los Muertos?

added.title: Scare Contest
added.description: Blippi wonders is it really fun to be scared?

added.title: Bath Song
added.description: Ella gets covered in mud so she goes into Mei's farmhouse to have a bath.

added.title: Old Macdonald
added.description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

added.title: Leader of the Pack
added.description: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden.

added.title: Lightning Bugs Sylvester
added.description: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

added.title: Flush Hour
added.description: The babies learn the purpose of toilets.

added.title: I Strain
added.description: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

added.title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
added.description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

added.title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
added.description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

removed.title: Los Supervillanso se Unen
removed.description: Después de una pausa en las payasadas alienígenas, un inquieto Ben les sugiere a Max y Gwen que podría ser un mejor héroe si fuera solo. Pero cuando Vilgax consigue la ayuda de Zombozo para construir un mecanismo hipnotizador gigante para hipnotizar al mundo entero, Ben debe replantearse su estrategia si quiere derrotar al equipo de supervillanos.

removed.title: Nuggets de Pollo de Sabiduria
removed.description: Cuando Ben y Max comienzan a discutir, Ben se convierte en Fuego para desahogarse, contra la voluntad de Max. Pero una vez que el Dr. Animo lo ve y convierte a Max en un pollo, Ben debe enmendar su error si quiere salvar a su Abuelo y detener al Dr. Animo.

removed.title: Isla Dyer
removed.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

removed.title: Los de Arriba Contra Atacan
removed.description: Cole y los de abajo llegan para rescatar a los Ninjas. Para ello, Cole tendrá que recuperar las espadas legendarias, las Espadas de la Liberación.

removed.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
removed.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

removed.title: Nivel Trece
removed.description: Cyrus Borg descubre un secreto sobre Primer Imperio y  los ninjas enfrentan al Mecánico que escapó e intenta alcanzar el Nivel 13 para entrar al juego.

removed.title: Todo Enrollado
removed.description: Cuando Ben se impacienta con el ritmo lento de la jardinería, se convierte en O-E Overflow para acelerar las cosas y, por accidente, inunda el jardín de la comunidad.

removed.title: El Hijo de Lilly
removed.description: iLa batalla por el destino de la Montaña Shintaro concluye!

removed.title: Teman a la Niebla
removed.description: Mientras Max intenta llevar a Ben y Gwen al Monumento de las Cuatro Esquinas antes del atardecer, un banco de niebla siniestra envuelve la carretera y obliga a Max a conducir a la velocidad de un caracol. Pero una vez que Fogg cobra vida y ataca el Rust Bucket, el equipo Tennyson debe trabajar unido si se quieren llegar sanos y salvos.

removed.title: Puedo Quedarmelo?
removed.description: Tras toparse con una adorable criatura, híbrido de gato, perro y conejo, Ben no hace caso al consejo del abuelo Max y se lleva al animal a escondidas al Chatarra. Pero pronto empiezan los problemas porque ila creación del Dr. Animal lo delata!

removed.title: Bengeance is Mine
removed.description: Vilgax' former lackey Psyphon is elated when his master returns.

removed.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
removed.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

removed.title: An American Benwolf in London
removed.description: Ben and Rook are called to London England to investigate the Forever Knights' latest activities.

removed.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
removed.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

removed.title: Ready to Rumble
removed.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

removed.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
removed.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

removed.title: Don't Drink the Water
removed.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

removed.title: Animo Crackers
removed.description: Dr. Animo from the future comes back to the present to help himself defeat Ben once and for all. (Introducing new Ben alien, Gutrot.)

removed.title: Divided We Stand
removed.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

removed.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
removed.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.
